Ugh! I‚Äôve never had so much difficulty getting my own money! Never again!!

I have been with PayPal since 2007, I buy and sell on EBay, and also use PayPal for personal and business use outside of PayPal. I sold an item on EBay but the buyer was having issues logging into PayPal through EBay so they sent me the money through PayPal Goods & Services. It‚Äôs been 2 days and my money is still being held, item has already shipped and I added the tracking number to the PayPal transaction. When I call I am told it is the automatic security protocol and it is not anything that can be corrected by a person. I asked how long the hold is, I was told ‚ÄúOh, we‚Äôre not told that, this way if a scammer calls trying to steal money, we can‚Äôt tell them when to try and transfer the money again. The hold is for as long as the security system wants it to be and that‚Äôs solely controlled by the computer system.‚Äù Seriously? A computer, who does not have a mortgage, a family, bills, or a life, is in sole control of when I can have my money. The sale was for over $1,000 and I even added money to the account at the recommendation of a PayPal associate to ‚Äútrick the system, since you‚Äôre adding money from the account you‚Äôre trying to transfer to so you can‚Äôt possibly be stealing.‚Äù Now that money is stuck in ‚Äúcomputer-controlled hold‚Äù also. Customer Service has been rude, unhelpful, and unknowledgeable. I can believe the lack of competency and that no one can do anything to get me my money. I mean they had me create a second account and try to transfer it there and then literally said ‚Äúwell, beats me!‚Äù when it did not work. Very frustrating, just lost a loyal long-time customer and her long-time customer parents, family, and friends.
Why $43.80 charge on a (US Domestic) transfer of $1500?  I WAS NOT NOTIFIED of this whatsoever and will not be using PayPal any longer if this is normal. Its exorbitant.   Doug White

And yes I understand this is basically 0 but I don‚Äôt understand why I gives me this unnecessary number instead of just 0. I‚Äôve tested this exact calculation on a number of other apps and even physical calculators as well as the standard iPhone app and they all give me 0. This is a really fantastic sudoku app, and I use it pretty much daily. However, the developer no longer supports it.   One major issue that has cropped up is that it frequently serves puzzles that are one or two grades above what you choose. So choose ‚Äúmild‚Äù, and you‚Äôre dealing with an ‚Äúintricate‚Äù puzzle. It‚Äôs not consistent, though. And what‚Äôs worse is that there‚Äôs no indication this has happened until you find yourself stumped on what should be a puzzle that requires no advanced moves.   Beyond that, the ‚Äúbest‚Äù time displayed will change pretty constantly while you‚Äôre playing a puzzle, so you won‚Äôt know what your actual record is until you beat it. And just a complaint, the ‚Äúlessons‚Äù for advanced moves, etc., are incomprehensible. You could have just sat on a keyboard and created clearer instructions than what‚Äôs there.

Great app, not for beginners as you need to have more than a basic knowledge of how to read and interpret radar on the map. Once you are able to understand you will discover how much this app has to offer. I have the base app without a subscription and that is good enough for me. Radar updates very quickly. Kansas City was nearly slammed with an EF4 tornado in May of this year (2019) and RadarScope displayed accurate velocity to pinpoint where the mile wide tornado was located. I was able to monitor the debris field as well using correlation coefficient. This app is strictly radar and is best used with other apps such as The Weather Channel for forecasts. This is my go to radar app. Fantastic. The only change I would make would be a more detailed map.

author: Oxydev
content: Just wanted to write a review on this to add a positive one to the collection. It only takes a little patience to let the app do what it does. It is a very simple app. You create the custom fields you want in a form and then the app gives you some code to add to where you want the form to show. Once someone fills out the form, and the review is approved, it will display under the form. It does not display instantly. It took a few hours for mine to display but it does work very well. There is nothing else to do. Just add the little string of code into where you want it to show up and that's it. Then your job is to just approve the reviews. The reviews are stored in product meta fields, so you can get the Metafields Editor app and edit something if you need to.
